�򸫤� ��ͻ�ⱥ��ﳲ����������ϥ�����  �����륹�����ˤ�ꤪ�ҥ��ޤυ��󥿡��ͥåȥх󥭥󥰤υѥ�������������˼����������ȯ�����ƥ��ޤ����ѥ��������υ������ƥ��к��ˤ����մꤤ�ޤ���  ���󥿡��ͥåȥх󥭥󥰤��������ѥˤ����մꤤ�ޤ���  ���������ԥ�̾�򤫤��ä��կ����żҥ᡼��ˤ����դ���������  �ݥåץ��åײ��̤ʤɤˤ�������˥��󥿡��ͥåȥх󥭥󥰤ʤɤθŀ;������߼�����ȥ����ⱥ�ˤ����դ���������  ��������󥿡��ͥåȥх󥭥󥰤ˤ�����ź������ssl �פν�λ�ˤĥ��� ���󥿡��ͥåȥх󥭥󥰤ȥ� ���¤򤪻����ǥʤ����ϥ����� ���������å�����ɡ��ץ�ȥ� �������� ��������� ��������� ���υڡ����ξ�������� �ŀͤτ��ҥ��� ���ƥξ��ʡ������ӥ����� ����򤿤�롦�դ ����ˤ��ʤ��� �����ڤ�� �����ˤĥ��� ���������ʹ���ƥߤ� ����ˤĥ���ĵ�� ���³��ߤτ����� ź�ޤτ����� ˡ�ͤτ��ҥ��� ����ˡ�ͤτ��ҥ��� ��ͻˡ�ͤτ��ҥ��� ������ȥγ����� �ŀ����ȥγ����ޤ� ir��֥�� ��̳�ϥ���� ������ϣ���� ir�������� ���������ԥˤĥ��� �ȥåץ�å����� ��ҿ��� ���������ԥ��롼�� �б����ˡ����� ���׶�̳�γ��� ���⳰���� �ҳ�׸���ư��csr��ư�� ���������ԥ��롼�פρ֥ե��ǥ����꡼���ǥ�ƥ����������ˡ� �������ȱ��γ������ ��ͻ�߳경�������� �żҹ��� �˥����꡼�� ���ѿ��� ��´���� ����ժ��� �и��ժ��� ���󥿡��󥷥å� ��ͷ���� ���ȶ�ʬ�ѹ��δ����� �ܵҷ�ʬ�ѹ��δ����� �ŀ;����ݸ����� ˡ�ͤτ��ҥ��޾���ζ�ͭ�ˤĥ��� ������ȿ�������� �ܥ����ȥτ����ѥˤ����ä� ������ҥ��������� ��ͽ��ͻ���� �����̳��ĺ���ж������ �����������ܾڷ��ȶ��񡢰��̼���ˡ�ͷ�ͻ��ʪ����ȶ��� copyright  aozora bank ltd all rights reserved aozora bank  wikipedia aozora bank from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search aozora bank ltd あおぞら type public kk limited traded as tyo  fwb aon otc pink aozoy industry money center banks predecessor nippon credit bank founded april   years ago  headquarters chiyoda tokyo japan key people brian f prince chairman shinsuke baba president and ceo products time deposits investment trusts individual annuity insurance telephone banking services atm alliances personal loans asset management consulting services  total assets ¥ b jpy sep  number of employees  bank only  website wwwaozorabankcojp aozora bank ltd あおぞら kabushikigaisha aozora ginkō lit blue sky bank is a japanese commercial bank that offers service in  branches in japan and in  overseas representative offices as of july  contents  history  locations  see also  references  external links historyedit aozora bank is the successor of the nippon credit bank ncb which was founded in  as the nippon fudosan bank under a special government trust banking license alongside the longterm credit bank of japan ltcb nippon fudosan bank was itself based on the remaining assets of the bank of joseon in japan in december  ncb was brought under government control in order to deal with its extraordinary amount of bad debt left over from the crash of the japanese asset price bubble in the early s at the time the bank was approximately ¥ billion in debt an investor group led by softbank orix and tokio marine  fire insurance co purchased ncb in  for ¥ billion as part of this deal the government included a defect warranty provision  kashi tanpo jōkō to the effect that ncb could demand within the next three years that the government purchase any claims which had fallen by twenty percent or more from value a similar provision had controversially been offered to the purchasers of ltcb which had recently been similarly purchased from the government and renamed shinsei bank aozora applied this provision conservatively in order to write off ¥ billion in bad debts owed by about  companies in contrast to shinsei bank the contemporaneous successor of the longterm credit bank which wrote off nearly three times as much and was criticized in political circles for doing so the sale of ncb to softbank was viewed as a precedent for the licensing of sony bank seven bank and other new banking platforms in japan the bank was renamed aozora in  softbank initially planned to make aozora an investment bank for internetrelated companies however softbank was unsuccessful in obtaining the cooperation of the financial services agency and sold its  stake to cerberus capital management in september  for ¥ billion aozora launched operations as a retail bank on april   and opened its first new branch in nihonbashi on november  aozora bank was listed as the no  unsecured creditor to lehman brothers with about  million usd in bank loans to the investment bank as it filed for chapter  bankruptcy in september  by comparison the second largest unsecured creditor was mizuho bank with  million and third largest citibank hong kong branch with  million on december   aozora bank announced that it had ¥ billion exposure to the bernard l madoff ponzi scheme on april   aozora bank and shinsei bank announced negotiations to integrate their operations in the summer of  with an eye toward an eventual merger banks had been hit by losses in the us subprime market the talks collapsed in may  amid disputes over capitalization and business strategy as well as the abatement of the  financial crisis aozora acquired japan wealth management securities in  merging it with existing subsidiary aozora securities in  in january  cerberus announced that it would sell most of its stake in aozora cutting its total share from  percent to  percent cerberus sold this last portion of its stake to barclays for distribution to other investors in august  ending cerberuss shareholding in aozora locationsedit aozora headquarters in tokyo aozoras head office is located in the kudan area of chiyoda city tokyo near yasukuni shrine the bank has retail branches in chiba fukuoka hiroshima kanazawa kyoto nagoya osaka namba and umeda sapporo sendai takamatsu tokyo ikebukuro jiyugaoka nihonbashi shibuya shinjuku and ueno and yokohama aozora also has representative offices in new york singapore seoul jakarta and shanghai and financing subsidiaries in the cayman islands hong kong luxembourg the united kingdom and the united states see alsoedit list of investors in bernard l madoff securities list of banks list of banks in japan referencesedit  corporate history retrieved on june    a b company profile retrieved on june    directors and auditors retrieved on february    corporate brochure  page three archived september   at the wayback machine retrieved on july  